<section id="steps">
  <title>Set up an additional monitor</title>
  <p>To set up an additional monitor, connect the monitor to your computer. If
  your system does not recognize it immediately, or you would like to adjust
  the settings:</p>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>Click on the <gui>User Menu</gui> on the bottom left-hand corner of
      your screen, then click on <gui>Settings</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Click on <gui>Displays</gui> to open the panel.</p>
    </item>
<!-- It is not possible to switch monitors off or on in 3.10
    <item>
      <p>Click on the monitor that you would like to activate or deactivate,
      then switch it <gui>ON/OFF</gui>.</p>
    </item>-->
    <item>
      <p>The monitor with the bottom bar is
      the main monitor. To change which monitor is treated as "main", click on
      the bottom bar and drag it over to the monitor which you want to set as the
      "main" monitor.</p>
    </item>
<!-- This does not work in 3.10 like this
    <item>
      <p>To change the "position" of a monitor, click on it and drag it to the
      desired position.</p>
      <note>
        <p>If you would like both monitors to display the same content, check
        the <gui>Mirror displays</gui> box.</p>
      </note>
    </item>
-->
    <item>
      <p>To rotate the orientation of the monitor, click on it and use the
      buttons with the arrows to rotate it.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>When you are happy with your settings, click <gui>Apply</gui> and then
      click <gui>Keep Changes</gui>.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>
